      <div class="article-body">
        <p>The kitchen is much more than a place to prepare food. It's the heart of the home, where the family gathers every morning, where conversations are shared while cooking, where children do their homework while you prepare dinner. A well-designed kitchen not only improves your home's functionality but transforms your daily quality of life.</p>

        <p>At ReformaT Houston we have been designing and building kitchens in Houston, The Woodlands, Sugar Land, and Katy for over 20 years. Each project is unique because every family has different needs. We don't sell prefabricated kitchens or generic solutions. We create personalized spaces that reflect your lifestyle, optimize your routine, and add real value to your property.</p>

        <img src="/images/kitchens-800.webp" alt="Modern kitchen completely finished by ReformaT Houston with premium finishes" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1200" height="800" />

        <h2>The Work Triangle: The Science Behind Design</h2>

        <p>Every professional kitchen design is based on the "work triangle," an architectural concept that optimizes distances between the three most used points: the sink, the stove, and the refrigerator. The ideal distance between these points should be between 4 and 9 feet, creating a triangle with a total perimeter of 13 to 26 feet.</p>

        <p>Why is this so important? Because a poorly designed kitchen forces you to walk unnecessary miles each week. We calculate that in an inefficient kitchen, a person walks up to 2 additional miles per week just preparing meals. Multiply that by 10 years and you'll understand why ergonomic design is not a luxury, it's a necessity.</p>

        <h3>Layout Types That Work</h3>

        <p><strong>L-Shaped Kitchen:</strong> Ideal for medium spaces. Uses two perpendicular walls, leaving free space for a dining table or central island. Perfect for families who use the kitchen as a social area.</p>

        <p><strong>U-Shaped Kitchen:</strong> Maximizes storage and work surfaces. All three sides of the triangle are clearly defined, creating an efficient workflow. Recommended for serious cooks who need plenty of space.</p>

        <p><strong>Kitchen with Island:</strong> The most versatile and modern option. The island serves as a preparation zone, informal dining area, storage space, and social point. Requires minimum 10x10 feet of free space to function properly.</p>

        <p><strong>Galley Kitchen:</strong> For narrow spaces or small apartments. All cabinetry is concentrated on a single wall, optimizing every inch. The challenge is maintaining a functional work triangle in reduced spaces.</p>

        <h2>Materials That Last Decades</h2>

        <p>The difference between a kitchen that lasts 5 years and one that lasts 25 is in the materials. We don't skimp on quality because we know a kitchen is used intensively every day. Every material we select has been tested under real domestic use conditions.</p>

        <h3>Cabinets: The Foundation of Your Kitchen</h3>

        <p>We work with solid wood cabinets (oak, maple, cherry), high-quality veneers, and moisture-resistant melamine for specific areas. All our cabinets include soft-close hinges and drawers, full-extension guides, and customizable interiors.</p>

        <h3>Countertops: Beauty Meets Functionality</h3>

        <p>We offer quartz (Caesarstone, Silestone), granite, quartzite, marble, and compact porcelain. Each material has specific characteristics: quartz is non-porous and low maintenance; granite offers unique natural patterns; quartzite combines beauty and resistance; marble provides timeless elegance.</p>

        <h3>Backsplashes: Protection and Style</h3>

        <p>The backsplash protects walls from water, grease, and heat while adding visual personality. We install ceramic subway tiles, porcelain mosaics, glass tiles, natural stone, and large-format panels.</p>

        <h2>Our Process: From Vision to Reality</h2>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Initial Consultation:</strong> We visit your home in Houston, The Woodlands, Sugar Land, or Katy. We listen to your needs, assess the space, discuss styles and budgets.</li>
          <li><strong>Preliminary Design:</strong> We create 2D and 3D plans so you can visualize the final result before construction begins.</li>
          <li><strong>Detailed Quote:</strong> Transparent budget with itemized costs. No surprises, no hidden charges.</li>
          <li><strong>Material Selection:</strong> We guide you through choosing cabinets, countertops, flooring, fixtures, and appliances.</li>
          <li><strong>Construction:</strong> Our experienced team executes the project with precision, cleanliness, and respect for your home.</li>
          <li><strong>Final Delivery:</strong> Thorough inspection, cleaning, and explanation of care and maintenance.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Investment That Adds Value</h2>

        <p>A professionally remodeled kitchen is one of the best investments you can make in your home. According to Remodeling Magazine's Cost vs. Value Report, kitchen remodels in Houston recover 70-85% of their value at resale. But beyond financial return, you gain:</p>

        <ul>
