  <FAQ items={[
    { q: "How long does a kitchen remodel take in Houston?", a: "A typical kitchen remodel takes 4-8 weeks depending on complexity. Simple updates may take 2-3 weeks, while complete renovations with layout changes can take 8-12 weeks. We provide a detailed timeline before starting." },
    { q: "Do I need permits for kitchen remodeling in Houston?", a: "Yes, most kitchen remodels in Houston require permits, especially if you're moving plumbing, electrical, or walls. We handle all permit applications and inspections as part of our service." },
    { q: "What's the average cost of kitchen remodeling in Houston?", a: "In Houston, kitchen remodels range from $5,000 for basic updates to $50,000+ for luxury renovations. Mid-range projects typically fall between $15,000-$30,000. We offer options for every budget." },
    { q: "Can I live in my home during kitchen remodeling?", a: "Yes, most clients remain in their homes during remodeling. We work efficiently to minimize disruption and can set up a temporary kitchen area if needed." },
    { q: "Do you help with appliance selection?", a: "Absolutely! We provide guidance on appliance selection based on your needs, kitchen layout, and budget. We have partnerships with major brands and can often secure better pricing." }
  ]} />
  
